Passage-9
 India faces a challenging immediate future in energy and climate policy-making. The problems are multiple: sputtering fossil fuel production capabilities;
 limited access to electricity and modern cooking fuel for the poorest; rising fuel imports in an unstable global energy context;
 continued electricity pricing and governance challenges leading to its costly deficits or surplus supply;
 and not least, growing environmental contestation around land, water and air. But all is not bleak: growing energy efficiency programmes;
 integrated urbanisation and transport policy discussions; inroads to enhancing energy access and security;
 and bold renewable energy initiatives, even if not fully conceptualised, suggest the promise of transformation.
